name: Laurien Magee
description:
Burnt at the stake as part of the Islandmagee witch trial, Ireleand, 1710

Laurien was one of the eight women that Mary Dunbar claimed were the witches that had attacked her in spectral form. She was found guilty of Witchcraft along with the seven other women 

Records during this time were lost during the Irish Civil War when the Public Records Office were burned; because of this exact records of what happened to Mary Dunbar and the eight women convicted were lost

One of a series working with AI to give face to women executed as witches; these form part of a broader collection of Horror Portraits at www.horrorportraits.xyz

#WitchingHourOnHEN 

Can be used as #PFP and #wallpaper

PNG 4800 x 4800
